%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221049%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENew%20research%20hones%20in%20on%20the%20reasons%20why%20your%20cat%20may%20be%20scratching%20up%20your%20furniture.%3Cp%3ESorayut%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20team%20discovered%20that%20naturally%20aggressive%20and%20disruptive%20cats%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20scratch%2C%20as%20well%20as%20cats%20who%20tended%20to%20play%20a%20lot%20and%20spent%20more%20time%20awake%20at%20night.%20But%20the%20research%20also%20showed%20there%20was%20more%20to%20the%20story%20than%20just%20kitty%20personality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cats'%20environments%20played%20a%20key%20role%20as%20well.%20%26quot%3BOne%20noteworthy%20finding%20is%20the%20influence%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20child%20at%20home%20on%20the%20high%20level%20of%20scratching%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20reported%20in%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Fjournals%2Fveterinary-science%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffvets.2024.1403068%2Ffull%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20published%20on%20July%202%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Frontiers%20in%20Veterinary%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20girl%20sits%20on%20the%20floor%20and%20feeds%20a%20grey%20cat%20from%20her%20hand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6688448c268f62ba18a7d8d5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222327%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECats%20and%20children%20may%20not%20be%20the%20best%20roommates%2C%20according%20to%20new%20research.%3Cp%3Eanastas_%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETurns%20out%2C%20cats%20don't%20seem%20to%20enjoy%20sharing%20a%20home%20with%20children%20all%20that%20much%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20the%20ones%20in%20this%20study.%20Children%20can%20stress%20cats%20out%2C%20which%20then%20leads%20the%20animals%20to%20scr