0decisively%20for%20change%2C%20for%20national%20renewal%20and%20a%20return%20of%20politics%20to%20public%20service%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2061-year-old%20said%20in%20his%20first%20speech%20as%20PM.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20work%20of%20change%20begins%20immediately%2C%20but%20have%20no%20doubt%2C%20we%20will%20rebuild%20Britain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Sorry'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20sombre%20Rishi%20Sunak%20conceded%20defeat%20during%20a%20torrid%20night%20for%20his%20Conservatives%20that%20claimed%20the%20scalps%20of%20at%20least%2012%20of%20his%20senior%20cabinet%20colleagues%20--%20and%20his%20predecessor%20Liz%20Truss.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20disastrous%2049-day%20tenure%20effectively%20sealed%20the%20Tories'%20fate%20with%20the%20public%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20her%20unfunded%20tax%20cuts%20spooked%20markets%20and%20crashed%20the%20pound.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20leaving%20Downing%20Street%20for%20the%20final%20time%20as%20prime%20minister%2C%20Sunak%20said%20%26quot%3Bsorry%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20public%20and%20revealed%20that%20he%20would%20step%20down%20as%20Tory%20leader%20once%20formal%20arrangements%20for%20a%20successor%20are%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELabour%20raced%20past%20the%20326%20seats%20needed%20to%20secure%20an%20overall%20majority%20in%20the%20650-seat%20House%20of%20Commons%20at%200400%20GMT%2C%20with%20the%20final%20result%20expected%20on%20Saturday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20of%201700%20GMT%20on%20Friday%2C%20the%20party%20had%20won%20412%20seats%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20with%20only%20one%20result%20left%20to%20declare%2C%20giving%20it%20a%20majority%20of%20174.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tories%20won%20just%20121%20seats%20--%20a%20record%20low%20--%20with%20the%20right-wing%20vote%20apparently%20spliced%20by%20Nigel%20Farage's%20anti-immigration%20Reform%20UK%20party%2C%20which%20picked%20up%20five%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20boost%20for%20the%20centrists%2C%20the%20smaller%20opposition%20Liberal%20Democrats%20ousted%20the%20Scottish%20National%20Party%20as%20the%20third-biggest%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorld%20reaction%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20buck%20a%20trend%20among%20Britain's%20closest%20Western%20allies%2C%20with%20the%20far-right%20in%20France%20eyeing%20power%20and%20Donald%20Trump%20looking%20set%20for%20a%20return%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongratulations%20came%20in%20from%20European%20leaders%2C%20including%20Germany's%20Chancellor%20Olaf%20Scholz%2C%20who%20said%20Starmer%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%2C%20very%20successful%26quot%3B%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20said%20the%20two%20countries%20would%20%26quot%3Bcontinue%20to%20be%20reliable%20allies%20through%20thick%20and%20thin%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEx-US%20president%20Donald%20Trump%20congratulated%20his%20admirer%20Farage%20on%20winning%20election%20to%20the%20UK%20parliament%20at%20his%20eighth%20attempt%2C%20but%20noticeably%20neglected%20to%20mention%20Starmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%20London's%20busy%20Waterloo%20station%2C%2049-year-old%20engagement%20officer%20Ramsey%20Sargent%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bmomentous%20election%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20very%20rocky%20over%20the%20last%20few%20months%20and%20years.%20I'm%20really%20excited%20to%20see%20what%20happens%20next%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Catastrophic'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20tendered%20his%20resignation%20to%20the%20king%20shortly%20after%20returning%20to%20London%20from%20his%20rural%20constituency%20in%20northern%20England%2C%20where%20the%20depth%20of%20his%20party's%20defeat%20quickly%20became%20apparent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Tories'%20worst%20previous%20election%20result%20was%20156%20seats%20in%201906.%20Former%20leader%20William%20Hague%20told%20Times%20Radio%20this%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20catastrophic%20result%20in%20historic%20terms%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Tim%20Bale%2C%20politics%20professor%20at%20Queen%20Mary%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20as%20catastrophic%20as%20some%20were%20predicting%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20Tories%20would%20now%20need%20to%20decide%20how%20best%20to%20fight%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBrexit%20champion%20Farage%20has%20made%20no%20secret%20of%20his%20aim%20to%20take%20over%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20massive%20gap%20on%20the%20centre-right%20of%20British%20politics%20and%20my%20job%20is%20to%20fill%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20after%20a%20comfortable%20win%20in%20Clacton%2C%20eastern%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETo-do%20list%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELabour's%20resurgence%20is%20a%20stunning%20turnaround%20from%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20hard-left%20former%20leader%20Jeremy%20Corbyn%20took%20the%20party%20to%20its%20worst%20defeat%20since%201935%20in%20an%20election%20dominated%20by%20Brexit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer%20took%20over%20in%20early%202020%20and%20set%20about%20moving%20the%20party%20back%20to%20the%20centre%2C%20purging%20the%20infighting%20and%20anti-Semitism%20that%20cost%20it%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpinion%20polls%20consistently%20put%20Labour%2020%20points%20ahead%20of%20the%20Tories%20since%20Truss's%20resignation%2C%20giving%20an%20air%20of%20inevitability%20about%20a%20Labour%20win%20--%20the%20first%20since%20Tony%20Blair%20in%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20count%20neared%20the%20end%2C%20the%20gap%20was%20around%2011%20percent%2C%20with%20Labour%20looking%20set%20to%20win%20fewer%20votes%20than%20it%20did%20in%202019%2C%20partly%20reflecting%20a%20lower%20turnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarmer%20faces%20a%20daunting%20in-tray%2C%20from%20anaemic%20economic%20growth%20to%20overstretched%20and%20underfunded%20public