0the%20married%20mother%20of%20two%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Iron%20chancellor'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReeves%20recently%20told%20company%20bosses%20that%20Labour%20had%20become%20%26quot%3Bthe%20natural%20party%20of%20British%20business%26quot%3B%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20party%20would%20show%20%26quot%3Biron%20discipline%26quot%3B%20over%20public%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20comments%20drew%20comparisons%20with%20'Iron%20Lady'%20Margaret%20Thatcher%2C%20Britain's%20first%20woman%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20Conservative%20leader%20Thatcher%2C%20who%20privatised%20key%20sectors%20after%20becoming%20prime%20minister%20in%201979%2C%20Reeves%20wants%20a%20form%20of%20renationalisation%2C%20notably%20for%20energy%2C%20as%20she%20takes%20inspiration%20from%20policy%20enacted%20by%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELabour%20has%20pledged%20to%20create%20Great%20British%20Energy%2C%20a%20publicly%20owned%20company%20that%20would%20spearhead%20funding%2C%20alongside%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bgreen%26quot%3B%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJames%20Wood%2C%20senior%20teaching%20associate%20in%20political%20economy%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%2C%20said%20Labour%20and%20Reeves%20were%20seeking%20a%20%26quot%3Bresponsible%26quot%3B%20approach%20to%20the%20public%20purse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20she%20talks%20about%20being%20an%20iron%20chancellor%2C%20I%20think%20what%20she%20means%20is%3A%20we're%20going%20to%20balance%20the%20books%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20responsible%20--%20and%20we're%20going%20to%20try%20and%20get%20Britain's%20economy%20running...%20in%20a%20responsible%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELondon-born%20Reeves%20tapped%20into%20public%20anger%20over%20Sunak's%20predecessor%20Liz%20Truss%2C%20whose%20unfunded%202022%20mini-budget%20crashed%20the%20pound%20and%20sent%20mortgage%20rates%20soaring%2C%20worsening%20a%20cost-of-living%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20want%20to%20distance%20themselves%20from%20fiscal%20irresponsibility%2C%20not%20making%20big%20promises%20about%20spending%20that%20they%20can't%20possibly%20keep%2C%26quot%3B%20Wood%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBanking%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReeves%2C%20whose%20parents%20were%20teachers%2C%20is%20no%20stranger%20to%20outmanoeuvring%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20became%20British%20girls'%20chess%20champion%20aged%2014%20before%20studying%20philosophy%2C%20politics%20and%20economics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Oxford%2C%20which%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20Master's%20degree%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%2C%20she%20worked%20as%20an%20economist%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20first%20at%20the%20Bank%20of%20England%20before%20switching%20to%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20for%20British%20retail%20bank%20HBOS%2C%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%20struck%20in%202008%2C%20resulting%20in%20her%20employer%20receiving%20a%20huge%20bailout%2C%20along%20with%20other%20lenders%2C%20from%20Gordon%20Brown's%20Labour%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20when%20the%20Conservatives%20entered%20power%20in%20a%20coalition%20with%20the%20Liberal%20Democrats%2C%20Reeves%20was%20elected%20Labour%20MP%20for%20Leeds%20West%20in%20northern%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEleven%20years%20later%2C%20Starmer%20appointed%20her%20as%20Labour's%20finance%20spokesperson.%20Her%20sister%20Ellie%20Reeves%20is%20also%20a%20Labour%20MP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1720194600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-07%2Faogtdje_rac